derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: abbreviation of obsolete wenchel 'child, servant, prostitute'; perhaps related to Old English wancol 'unsteady, inconstant'

entry.def: A wench was a girl or young woman who worked as a servant or served people food or drink.
